The paper focuses on analyzing the connecting architectures of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP), speech recognition, and image captioning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the topic of the paper. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category as RNNs are a popular tool in AI research. The paper also mentions long-term dependency problems, which are common in NLP, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper briefly mentions image captioning, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision), making it a less likely but still possible sub-category.
